        <!-- HighWire is implementing this so that there is one <Customer> element per title (i.e. <ReportItem>). So if an institution
             has two journals from the same publisher, that would be two <Customer> elements, even if they are under the same
             subscription. While it may be possible to produce output with slightly fewer rows if one <Customer> could have more
             than one embedded <ReportItem> element (which the schema allows), it is more straightforward - both for generating the
             output and for doing transforms - to have the element structure be consistent.
        -->
        <c:Customer>
                <c:Name>University of Notre Dame</c:Name>
